out of the bag on the lift and held it down,

264
00:12:29,572 --> 00:12:31,472
stuck the gun at his temple and fired.

265
00:12:32,572 --> 00:12:35,172
He then took Mr. Minowa out of the bag and sat him down

266
00:12:35,172 --> 00:12:36,872
and made him hold the gun.

267
00:12:36,872 --> 00:12:40,772
He then carried the bag and jumped off.

268
00:12:40,772 --> 00:12:42,872
There are two places where the space

269
00:12:42,872 --> 00:12:47,272
between the lift and the ground is only about 3 meters.

270
00:12:47,272 --> 00:12:50,172
The scratch that was found on the seat of the lift

271
00:12:50,172 --> 00:12:52,472
was one that was made when he shot Mr. Minowa.

272
00:12:52,472 --> 00:12:56,172
And the fact that Mr. Minowa was sitting on the left when on the lift,

273
00:12:56,172 --> 00:12:59,072
but was found sitting on the right side when found dead

274
00:12:59,072 --> 00:13:02,072
is evidence that this is what actually happened.

275
00:13:02,072 --> 00:13:03,872
It sure is difficult

276
00:13:03,872 --> 00:13:07,172
to shift the position of a dead person on a lift.

277
00:13:07,172 --> 00:13:09,172
But, when the gunshot was heard,

278
00:13:09,172 --> 00:13:11,172
Mr. Mimata was talking to me.

279
00:13:11,172 --> 00:13:13,572
That was probably the sound of a rocket fire cracker.

280
00:13:13,572 --> 00:13:15,172
After he wore the ski wear

281
00:13:15,172 --> 00:13:17,672
that he had ready by the place he got off the lift,

282
00:13:17,672 --> 00:13:19,772
he probably ignited the fuse of the rocket fire cracker

283
00:13:19,772 --> 00:13:21,972
with a lighted cigarette and poked it into a PET bottle.

284
00:13:21,972 --> 00:13:24,272
He fired it shifting the time a bit to make a witness for his alibi,

285
00:13:24,272 --> 00:13:30,872
by skiing down and talking to somebody when the sound is heard.

286
00:13:30,872 --> 00:13:33,872
But, where did he get the bag that was packed with snow?

287
00:13:33,872 --> 00:13:36,072
I just said that there are two places

288
00:13:36,072 --> 00:13:39,372
where that lift is only 3 meters away from the ground.

289
00:13:39,372 --> 00:13:41,772
That's where the bag with the upside down ski pole

290
00:13:41,772 --> 00:13:44,772
hooked onto it was place, and later carried up to the lift.

291
00:13:44,772 --> 00:13:47,372
I see. 3 meters to the ground...

292
00:13:47,372 --> 00:13:50,472
Ski poles are approximately 1 meter and 20 centimeters.

293
00:13:50,472 --> 00:13:53,072
If the string one side is hooked on to the other pole and connected,

294
00:13:53,072 --> 00:13:55,672
stretching over for it may make it reachable,

295
00:13:55,672 --> 00:13:58,472
but would it be possible to pick it up in that blizzard?

296
00:13:58,472 --> 00:14:01,372
No, no! Only one ski pole was used,

297
00:14:01,372 --> 00:14:03,172
and the remaining 1 meter...

298
00:14:03,172 --> 00:14:06,272
was made by wetting the string of the cloth bag

299
00:14:06,272 --> 00:14:08,572
with water and freezing it.

300
00:14:08,572 --> 00:14:11,372
That's how the remaining one meter was compensated for.

301
00:14:11,372 --> 00:14:13,772
The loops of both poles were upside down

302
00:14:13,772 --> 00:14:16,072
