303
00:14:16,072 --> 00:14:19,572
But I wonder if you can see that bag from on top the lift?

304
00:14:19,572 --> 00:14:21,172
I mean the blizzard was so bad

305
00:14:21,172 --> 00:14:22,372
that even the lift ahead couldn't be seen, right?

306
00:14:22,372 --> 00:14:24,972
Did you know that the space between one lift and the other

307
00:14:24,972 --> 00:14:27,472
has to be more than 6 seconds apart?

308
00:14:27,472 --> 00:14:29,372
The speed at which a lift moves

309
00:14:29,372 --> 00:14:31,972
is from 1.5 meters to 2 meters per second,

310
00:14:31,972 --> 00:14:34,272
which means that the space between one lift and the other

311
00:14:34,272 --> 00:14:36,272
is about 10 meters apart.

312
00:14:36,272 --> 00:14:38,472
Even if it is hard to something that is 10 meters apart,

313
00:14:38,472 --> 00:14:41,572
the bag that was only 3 meters apart could easily be seen.

314
00:14:41,572 --> 00:14:44,872
More so, if you know that the bag is already there...

315
00:14:44,872 --> 00:14:46,272
But, what proof do you have?

316
00:14:46,272 --> 00:14:48,172
I've got proof, too.

317
00:14:48,172 --> 00:14:50,172
If Mr. Mimata met with Ms. Tateishi

318
00:14:50,172 --> 00:14:54,072
and went directly to be interrogated in the lodge,

319
00:14:54,072 --> 00:14:56,372
he still should have it on him.

320
00:14:57,972 --> 00:15:01,472
The same ski wear that Mr. Minowa was wearing.

321
00:15:01,472 --> 00:15:05,472
Maybe you even have the bag that Mr. Minowa inside, too?

322
00:15:07,072 --> 00:15:09,372
I was enduring all this time.

323
00:15:09,372 --> 00:15:11,672
It was so hot.

324
00:15:11,672 --> 00:15:13,272
Mr. Mimata!

325
00:15:13,272 --> 00:15:14,872
So, you the one who did it, after all.

326
00:15:14,872 --> 00:15:17,572
Which means that you knew, director.

327
00:15:17,572 --> 00:15:18,772
Yeah.

328
00:15:18,772 --> 00:15:22,072
I thought that your skiing had improved in the end,

329
00:15:22,072 --> 00:15:26,472
but when I saw him dead, I realized it was you.

330
00:15:26,472 --> 00:15:28,172
But, why?

331
00:15:28,172 --> 00:15:30,072
I avenged the death of Mr. Mizukami

332
00:15:30,072 --> 00:15:33,172
who was supposed to become your husband.

333
00:15:33,172 --> 00:15:36,072
I killed Minowa using the same trick

334
00:15:36,072 --> 00:15:38,472
that was used to kill Mr. Mizukami 4 years ago.

335
00:15:38,472 --> 00:15:39,872
Just what do you mean?

336
00:15:39,872 --> 00:15:42,572
Remember 4 years ago, that day,

337
00:15:42,572 --> 00:15:45,172
Minowa was troubled surrounded by his fans,

338
00:15:45,172 --> 00:15:48,872
Mr. Mizukami said we can work something out.

339
00:15:48,872 --> 00:15:50,372
He meant that

340
00:15:50,372 --> 00:15:53,872
he would secretly put Minowa inside a bag and carrying him over.

341
00:15:53,872 --> 00:15:57,872
But Minowa took advantage of Mr. Mizukami's kindness and killed him.

342
00:15:57,872 --> 00:15:59,672
He killed Mr. Mizukami who was planning on quitting his job as a stuntman

343
00:15:59,672 --> 00:16:02,172
and become an actor!

344
00:16:02,172 --> 00:16:05,472
He told me when I held him at gun point.

345
00:16:05,472 --> 00:16:08,372
There's no way he can make a living as an actor.

346
00:16:08,372 --> 00:16:09,472
I'm sure that when he gets desperate,

347
00:16:09,472 --> 00:16:11,572
he is going to write a book on me and disclose everything!

348
00:16:11,572 --> 00:16:14,472
I guess he was scared.

349
00:16:14,472 --> 00:16:15,872
How ironic

350
00:16:15,872 --> 00:16:20,172
that a movie that is just the thing to carry out the revenge is to be shot.

351
00:16:20,172 --> 00:16:22,672
The fact is, I too, thought that the killer of the incident

352
00:16:22,672 --> 00:16:25,272
that happened 4 years ago was Minowa.

353
00:16:25,272 --> 00:16:28,072
That's why I decided to make this movie.

354
00:16:28,072 --> 00:16:30,072
I didn't reveal anything yet,

355
00:16:30,072 --> 00:16:31,572
but the real killer of this movie

356
00:16:31,572 --> 00:16:33,972
was scheduled to be Minowa, who was acting the role of a detective.

357
00:16:33,972 --> 00:16:35,972
The trick used is the same as was used 4 years ago

358
00:16:35,972 --> 00:16:37,972
as Mr. Mimata had just mentioned.

359
00:16:37,972 --> 00:16:42,472
I figured that he would give himself in if I showed him the script.

360
00:16:44,172 --> 00:16:46,772
I know that it's not for me, who quit being an officer to say,

361
00:16:46,772 --> 00:16:48,672
but if you knew so much,

362
00:16:48,672 --> 00:16:52,272
I would've wanted you to prevent this stupid murder.

363
00:16:52,272 --> 00:16:54,472
Revenge only breeds revenge,

364
00:16:54,472 --> 00:16:57,372
and the feeling of accomplishment vanishes on the spot...

365
00:16:57,372 --> 00:17:00,072
It's just like the snow that falls onto the palm of your hand.

366
00:17:06,372 --> 00:17:09,472
Well, we'll hear you out at the station.

367
00:17:09,472 --> 00:17:11,372
You'll come along too, won't you?

368
00:17:11,372 --> 00:17:15,672
Inspector, what about the intermediate school boy on the phone?

369
00:17:15,672 --> 00:17:18,472
He is telling of the exact same deduction of as that boy

370
00:17:18,472 --> 00:17:21,572
with the exact same timing.

371
00:17:21,572 --> 00:17:24,772
-What? -What?

372
00:17:24,772 --> 00:17:28,372
Heiji, why aren't you going with him?

373
00:17:28,372 --> 00:17:29,872
Idiot! If I leave,

374
00:17:29,872 --> 00:17:32,872
